# GL.iNet router admin password
#
# Copy this file to router_password.txt and put your actual router password in it.
#
#   cp router_password.txt.example router_password.txt
#   # then edit router_password.txt with the real password
#
# This file (router_password.txt) is gitignored.
# The contents will be mounted as a Docker secret and made available
# inside the web container as the environment variable GLINET_ROUTER_PASS.
#
# This is consumed by glinet_blacklist.py (GlinetClient) when the
# ChoreTracker webapp needs to manage MAC black/whitelists on the router.
your-router-admin-password-here
